    <bioghist encodinganalog="545" id="a2">
      <head>Biographical/Historical note</head>
      <p>Charles Curry was a merchant in Detroit in 1798. He was a Detroit agent for Robison andamp; Martin of Albany, New York, 1801-1803; partner of Hugh R. Martin, 18011808; county commissioner, 1803; Quartermaster, Legionary Corps, Michigan Militia, 1806. He became an American citizen in 1807. Curry died in Detroit in September 1810.  (Governor andamp; Judges journal, p. 196, Biography Index)</p>
    </bioghist>
